&TUTORIAL ------------------------ UTILITIES -------------------------- TUTORIAL
&NEXT SELECTION ===>%SELECT                             &
$
&                     -----------------------------------
&                     |            UTILITIES            |
                      -----------------------------------
$  THE&UTILITY$OPTION ALLOWS YOU TO SELECT ONE OF NINE UTILITIES LISTED BELOW.
   TO SELECT A UTILITY, ENTER A NUMBER FROM 1 TO 9 ON THE UTILITY SELECTION
   MENU, WHICH IS DISPLAYED WHEN OPTION 3 IS ENTERED ON THE PRIMARY OPTION MENU.

 THE FOLLOWING TOPICS ARE PRESENTED IN SEQUENCE, OR MAY BE SELECTED BY NUMBER:
    &1$- LIBRARY UTILITIES......PRINT INDEX OR ENTIRE DATA SET; PRINT, RENAME,
                                OR DELETE MEMBER; COMPRESS DATA SET
    &2$- DATA SET UTILITIES.....ALLOCATE, RENAME, DELETE, CATALOG, OR UNCATALOG
                                DATA SET; DISPLAY DATA SET INFORMATION
    &3$- MOVE/COPY UTILITY......MOVE OR COPY MEMBERS OR DATA SETS
    &4$- CATALOG MANAGEMENT.....DISPLAY OR PRINT CATALOG ENTRIES;
                                INITIALIZE OR DELETE PROJECT CATALOG POINTER
    &5$- RESET SPF STATISTICS...RESET SOURCE MEMBER STATISTICS
    &6$- HARDCOPY UTILITY.......INITIATE HARDCOPY OUTPUT
    &7$- VTOC UTILITY...........DISPLAY OR PRINT A DASD VTOC
    &8$- OUTLIST UTILITY........BROWSE, DELETE, OR PRINT HELD JOB OUTPUT
<ACTION>
1 SELECT CHAR(36) CURSOR;
2 SELECT CHAR(8) LIST(1  ,2  ,3   ,4   ,5  ,6  ,7  ,8   ,9)
               RETURN(TUL,TUD,TUMC,TUCM,TUR,TUH,TUV,TUOL,VTNOTSUP);
3 * CHAR(8) INIT('TTUTOR  ');
4 * CHAR(8) INIT('TP      ');
5 * CHAR(8) INIT('TUL     ');
<END>
